field.value:
The prototype validation strategy creates the js validation methods, based on input elements id that would be strange

if the object is:
class SomeDto
{
   public string Name ...


   [ValidateSameAs("Name")]
   public string Surname ...
}

the validation expects the html input element to have an id "SomeDto_name" rather than "SomeDto_Name", thus forcing a manual fix on the view, supplying the id in the needed format, to the FormHelper.TextField method.

suggested patch removes the .ToLowerInvariant calls on the target Id creation
